1
00:00:02,180 --> 00:00:05,090
Episode 4

2
00:00:09,080 --> 00:00:11,330
Hey, Crazy Hong!

3
00:00:12,680 --> 00:00:15,150
Jenny!

4
00:00:21,620 --> 00:00:25,580
Hey, come here for a sec.

5
00:00:28,230 --> 00:00:31,880
Today's scoop! A cute rookie dog companion has arrived.

6
00:00:31,880 --> 00:00:36,580
Should we all bark prettily for the conductor's new poodle? Woof woof!

7
00:00:36,580 --> 00:00:39,930
What's this all about?

8
00:00:39,930 --> 00:00:46,060
- Who took these pictures?
- Sinyeong Philharmonic's attention-seeker. The only one to have access to the anonymous community board.

9
00:00:46,060 --> 00:00:48,080
An attention-seeker did this?

10
00:00:48,080 --> 00:00:52,680
Yes. Her name is Yu Da Ra. She's this new stalker who knows how to get information.

11
00:00:52,680 --> 00:00:57,890
I don't know whether it's a guy or a girl, but my instinct tells me it's a b*tch.

12
00:00:57,890 --> 00:01:01,490
But, this was just to help Maestro Nam choose a gift.

13
00:01:01,490 --> 00:01:07,500
Hey, who cares about the truth? People just need someone to vent their anger at.

14
00:01:07,500 --> 00:01:10,980
Lighten up. At these times, you need to be brazen.

15
00:01:22,950 --> 00:01:29,000
I don't believe this! Did she really show up here?

16
00:01:34,050 --> 00:01:40,610
Hello, Principal. She's a newbie who came in today. She came to greet you first.

17
00:01:40,610 --> 00:01:44,600
Hello, I'm Hong Yi Yeong, the potential candidate for the second timpanist position.

18
00:01:44,600 --> 00:01:50,720
It is an honor to meet you. I have been watching your videos since I was in school.

19
00:01:55,100 --> 00:01:59,380
- Do you know that bastard didn't ask me for my opinion?
- Excuse me?

20
00:02:00,790 --> 00:02:06,190
We were looking for a timpanist, but he didn't even ask my opinion, although I'm the principal tympanist here.

21
00:02:06,190 --> 00:02:09,560
He by-passed and ignored me.

22
00:02:09,560 --> 00:02:13,740
Those of you who didn't eat breakfast, you should eat this.

23
00:02:17,240 --> 00:02:20,910
- Principal!
- Who is she?

24
00:02:20,910 --> 00:02:25,400
She's the new timpanist candidate. She's the oboe Principal.

25
00:02:25,400 --> 00:02:29,470
Hello. My name is Hong Yi Yeong. Please take care of me.

26
00:02:29,470 --> 00:02:36,260
Are you the new timpanist selected yesterday although we didn't need one? I heard you slept with Maestro Nam.

27
00:02:36,260 --> 00:02:38,040
Pardon?

28
00:02:38,040 --> 00:02:44,430
You look more innocent than in the pictures. I was waiting to see how thick-skinned you were.

29
00:02:45,540 --> 00:02:48,480
I didn't sleep with the conductor.

30
00:02:48,480 --> 00:02:53,190
What's so wrong with that you protest so much?   You can do that when your heart is full.

31
00:02:53,190 --> 00:03:00,510
But you need to protect yourself.  You don't want to be stabbed in the back.  Everyone here is taking it badly.

32
00:03:06,230 --> 00:03:08,380
Woof, woof!

33
00:03:09,800 --> 00:03:13,480
Wow, does she want a death note?

34
00:03:15,410 --> 00:03:21,220
No, just leave it. I just need to do better.

35
00:03:45,060 --> 00:03:48,990
I know a method to relax.

36
00:03:48,990 --> 00:03:53,210
Write the Chinese character for "person" three times in a row like this.

37
00:03:55,120 --> 00:03:59,840
- This is it?
- It works 100%.

38
00:04:29,400 --> 00:04:32,510
It's Ha Eun Ju!

39
00:04:32,510 --> 00:04:34,580
Ha Eun Ju...

40
00:04:34,580 --> 00:04:36,550
Why is she here...

41
00:04:45,730 --> 00:04:47,680
What are you?

42
00:04:55,990 --> 00:04:59,790
It's you, right? The b*tch who took a picture of me with Mun Jae Hyeong in the practice room.

43
00:04:59,790 --> 00:05:05,600
Have you lost it? Where do you think you are to be hitting me?

44
00:05:07,790 --> 00:05:10,400
Be careful with your fingers.

45
00:05:10,400 --> 00:05:15,670
Try pressing on that button carelessly one more time and I'll cut them off without anyone knowing.

46
00:05:39,460 --> 00:05:44,040
Do you think you will be safe?

47
00:05:47,340 --> 00:05:51,320
I'll sue you. Just watch me.

48
00:06:02,370 --> 00:06:04,970
Good morning!

49
00:06:09,570 --> 00:06:13,680
- Who is that?
- It's the first time I see him.

50
00:06:17,210 --> 00:06:21,480
Take a seat, everybody.

51
00:06:21,480 --> 00:06:25,240
From now on, you don't need to stand up when I come in.

52
00:06:28,820 --> 00:06:34,370
- Have you all been well?
- Yes.

53
00:06:34,370 --> 00:06:36,310
Yes.

54
00:06:36,310 --> 00:06:42,860
The response is quite bland. I wished that everyone was doing well and hoped that this day came faster.

55
00:06:42,860 --> 00:06:46,740
Since today is the first day, should we start by greeting the new members?

56
00:06:46,740 --> 00:06:53,090
First of all, the 2nd violinist, Ha Eun Ju.

57
00:07:00,160 --> 00:07:05,040
Next, the new timpanist Hong Yi Yeong.

58
00:07:07,300 --> 00:07:13,800
Nice to meet you. Please take care of me.

59
00:07:18,590 --> 00:07:25,200
And lastly, the guest pianist who captivated me, Mr. Jang Yun.

60
00:07:26,990 --> 00:07:29,730
Who's Jang Yun?

61
00:07:29,730 --> 00:07:33,650
- Pianist?
- Jang Yun?

62
00:07:42,600 --> 00:07:45,730
This is my sudden suggestion, in order to lighten the mood.

63
00:07:45,730 --> 00:07:49,570
I suggest we start by listening to a piece before starting the rehearsal. Is that alright?

64
00:07:49,570 --> 00:07:53,380
Yes.

65
00:07:53,380 --> 00:07:55,800
Shall we?

66
00:09:22,760 --> 00:09:24,850
Bravo!

67
00:09:29,570 --> 00:09:33,220
Wow!

68
00:09:50,940 --> 00:09:55,200
What's with you? Have you fallen for him?

69
00:09:55,200 --> 00:09:59,530
No way. That's not it at all.

70
00:09:59,530 --> 00:10:03,910
There was something.

71
00:10:03,910 --> 00:10:11,780
No there isn't. I was wondering where he came from, but he's pretty damn good. I heard he didn't go to a music college.

72
00:10:11,780 --> 00:10:18,560
- Really?
-Yeah. The board was opposed but Maestro Nam stubbornly insisted on bringing him in.

73
00:10:18,560 --> 00:10:23,730
- I see.
- What about you? Is it doable?

74
00:10:23,730 --> 00:10:26,760
No. It's killing me.

75
00:11:34,430 --> 00:11:36,490
Stop. Stop.

76
00:11:37,360 --> 00:11:39,410
Miss Hong Yi Yeong?

77
00:11:39,410 --> 00:11:42,410
You keep being late by half a beat.

78
00:11:42,410 --> 00:11:45,280
I'm so sorry. I'm so sorry.

79
00:11:45,280 --> 00:11:49,790
Be more in rhythm and add some emotion into it. Let's start again from the top.

80
00:12:22,000 --> 00:12:24,430
No, no. Stop.

81
00:12:28,000 --> 00:12:30,950
Should we do the timpani part again?

82
00:12:34,910 --> 00:12:37,680
I'm so sorry. I'm so sorry.

83
00:13:23,090 --> 00:13:25,720
Miss Hong Yi Yeong, are you going to keep doing  this?

84
00:13:25,720 --> 00:13:27,720
Like an amateur?

85
00:13:27,720 --> 00:13:29,570
Maestro!

86
00:13:30,920 --> 00:13:34,130
I'm sorry. My hands are sweating a lot. I'm sorry.

87
00:13:34,130 --> 00:13:36,480
Mr. Conductor, can we go again just once more?

88
00:13:36,480 --> 00:13:38,260
I'm sorry.

89
00:13:41,440 --> 00:13:43,410
Let's do this then.

90
00:13:43,410 --> 00:13:48,660
Let's wrap up the rehearsal for today. If the situation remains the same next time, we'll change the piece.

91
00:13:48,660 --> 00:13:50,570
Okay?

92
00:13:51,430 --> 00:13:53,220
That's all then.

93
00:14:35,680 --> 00:14:37,530
Give me my mallet.

94
00:14:37,530 --> 00:14:39,480
I don't want to.

95
00:14:43,360 --> 00:14:45,540
Why didn't you tell me you were a musician?

96
00:14:45,540 --> 00:14:49,870
When I told you about the Sinyeong Philharmonic audition, you didn't say anything either.

97
00:14:51,290 --> 00:14:53,470
You didn't ask.

98
00:14:58,170 --> 00:15:01,210
As I expected, you're so good at cursing with your face.

99
00:15:01,210 --> 00:15:04,870
Wow, it's scary. Here.

100
00:15:14,910 --> 00:15:17,730
You were clapping like a seal before.

101
00:15:17,730 --> 00:15:19,450
When did I?

102
00:15:19,450 --> 00:15:21,840
When I played Pororo.(An animated penguin loved by Korean children)

103
00:15:21,840 --> 00:15:23,810
I didn't clap like a seal.

104
00:15:23,810 --> 00:15:27,380
What do you mean? I saw you clapping like a seal.

105
00:15:28,390 --> 00:15:30,770
Alright, I did. What's it to you?

106
00:15:30,770 --> 00:15:35,170
You must be happy that you received applause because you played well, right?

107
00:15:37,700 --> 00:15:41,400
Should we go eat some meat? To celebrate us getting a job.

108
00:15:41,400 --> 00:15:45,430
Or should we go drink? We can also eat then.

109
00:15:45,430 --> 00:15:47,800
- We can sleep together, too.
- Hey!

110
00:15:49,730 --> 00:15:52,120
Are you having fun with me?

111
00:15:52,120 --> 00:15:54,170
Is my situation funny? Is it fun?

112
00:15:54,170 --> 00:15:56,370
Do I look like a joke?

113
00:15:56,370 --> 00:16:01,740
What kind of person... Can't you read in between the lines?

114
00:16:29,390 --> 00:16:33,090
Tone-deaf guy

115
00:16:42,290 --> 00:16:45,550
Tone-deaf guy

116
00:16:46,790 --> 00:16:48,100
Hello?

117
00:16:48,100 --> 00:16:52,290
I'm sorry. I'm not in the mood to talk on the phone.

118
00:16:52,290 --> 00:16:54,450
I'll pretend I heard you sing today.

119
00:16:54,450 --> 00:16:56,830
Don't be like that and come out.

120
00:16:56,830 --> 00:16:57,950
Excuse me?

121
00:16:57,950 --> 00:17:01,640
You must be feeling terrible, so you can't even sleep.

122
00:17:01,640 --> 00:17:05,270
I'm in front of the convenience store, so come out for a bit.

123
00:17:05,270 --> 00:17:10,370
Forget it. I don't feel like seeing you.

124
00:17:34,550 --> 00:17:38,940
You scared me. Move a little.

125
00:17:38,940 --> 00:17:42,410
I got this as a birthday gift. How is it?

126
00:17:42,410 --> 00:17:43,870
Does it suit me?

127
00:17:43,870 --> 00:17:47,040
Sure. A lot.

128
00:17:48,540 --> 00:17:51,330
You didn't even look properly.

129
00:17:59,620 --> 00:18:03,110
I met Professor Kang a while ago.

130
00:18:03,110 --> 00:18:07,610
Professor Kang Myeong Seok from the Instrumental Department of Sinyeong Music College.

131
00:18:07,610 --> 00:18:09,610
You know him well, right?

132
00:18:09,610 --> 00:18:11,570
Yes, I do.

133
00:18:13,630 --> 00:18:18,940
He suddenly asked me about Hong Yi Yeong.

134
00:18:18,940 --> 00:18:21,580
He asked me what she was up to.

135
00:18:22,440 --> 00:18:24,490
So, I told him.

136
00:18:24,490 --> 00:18:28,330
That Mr. Conductor found her and took her in.

137
00:18:29,880 --> 00:18:31,730
So?

138
00:18:34,220 --> 00:18:38,850
Now, you're paying attention to what I am saying.

139
00:18:38,850 --> 00:18:41,790
You're even pretending to listen.

140
00:19:03,480 --> 00:19:06,630
I slept with Hong Yi Yeong's boyfriend not too long ago.

141
00:19:06,630 --> 00:19:10,780
I wasn't in my right mind. I was drunk that day.

142
00:19:10,780 --> 00:19:15,680
To be honest, I also wanted to torment her.

143
00:19:17,120 --> 00:19:19,060
Who?

144
00:19:21,040 --> 00:19:25,560
Hong Yi Yeong. They broke up because of me.

145
00:19:26,830 --> 00:19:29,770
Why are you telling me this?

146
00:19:32,190 --> 00:19:34,810
You're interested in Hong Yi Yeong.

147
00:19:34,810 --> 00:19:36,390
Isn't that right?

148
00:19:36,390 --> 00:19:41,230
You held this audition because of her. Because you wanted to take her in.

149
00:19:41,230 --> 00:19:44,230
Your imagination is quite something.

150
00:19:46,890 --> 00:19:49,140
Don't smile.

151
00:19:50,000 --> 00:19:52,240
I'm so curious, it drives me crazy.

152
00:19:52,240 --> 00:19:53,890
Why do you care about her?

153
00:19:53,890 --> 00:19:57,970
You've been like this since a year ago. To be more precise, since her accident.

154
00:19:57,970 --> 00:19:59,860
What is the reason?

155
00:19:59,860 --> 00:20:02,360
Is it something I can't know about?

156
00:20:52,990 --> 00:20:56,200
Please be careful with the piano when going inside.

157
00:20:56,200 --> 00:20:57,890
Yes.

158
00:21:12,120 --> 00:21:12,740
What?

159
00:21:12,740 --> 00:21:14,920
A lot of things are strange. What is strange about that?

160
00:21:14,920 --> 00:21:16,330
It's just a coincidence.

161
00:21:16,330 --> 00:21:20,730
Yes, but we met coincidentally more than three times. How is it not strange?

162
00:21:20,730 --> 00:21:23,580
He gave me his number, then I saw him at the Sinyeong Philharmonic audition.

163
00:21:23,580 --> 00:21:27,290
And now, out of all this large neighborhood, he's moved right next to me.

164
00:21:27,290 --> 00:21:29,920
That's a kind of paranoia. Paranoia.

165
00:21:29,920 --> 00:21:33,980
You got his number because of that part-time job. Then, you told him you messed up the Sinyeong Philharmonic audition.

166
00:21:33,980 --> 00:21:35,500
So, they are not coincidences.

167
00:21:35,500 --> 00:21:39,890
Let's say you met a few times because you live in the same neighborhood.

168
00:21:39,890 --> 00:21:42,670
To be frank, how much does he know about you, that he would sell his house and move?

169
00:21:42,670 --> 00:21:43,810
It would be a waste of his money.

170
00:21:43,810 --> 00:21:46,300
That's true, but...

171
00:21:46,300 --> 00:21:49,710
He laughed at me rudely when our eyes met.

172
00:21:49,710 --> 00:21:52,470
He happened to move and it turns out I'm his neighbor,

173
00:21:52,470 --> 00:21:54,780
shouldn't it be normal to be surprised?

174
00:21:57,460 --> 00:22:01,200
Stop saying useless things and go eat breakfast. I need to go to a therapy session.

175
00:22:01,200 --> 00:22:03,540
Oh, I get it. Okay.

176
00:22:03,540 --> 00:22:05,840
I'll talk to you on the weekend at home.

177
00:22:11,170 --> 00:22:12,860
What are you?

178
00:22:12,860 --> 00:22:16,550
Where did you buy these clothes?

179
00:22:17,400 --> 00:22:19,370
I bought them online, why?

180
00:22:19,370 --> 00:22:22,300
Your taste is quite unique.

181
00:22:22,300 --> 00:22:24,850
What are you going to do today?

182
00:22:24,850 --> 00:22:26,560
Why are you asking this?

183
00:22:26,560 --> 00:22:28,510
There's no rehearsal today.

184
00:22:28,510 --> 00:22:32,990
After that rehearsal, you'll be fired anyway.

185
00:22:33,680 --> 00:22:35,640
What did you say?

186
00:22:37,010 --> 00:22:40,370
Let's hang out together and kill some time.

187
00:22:43,580 --> 00:22:47,430
Jang Yun, don't you have friends? You ask me to hang out together every time you see me.

188
00:22:47,430 --> 00:22:48,640
Are you interested in me?

189
00:22:48,640 --> 00:22:51,070
A lot. Aren't you?

190
00:22:51,070 --> 00:22:54,590
Not even one bit. Didn't you move in today?

191
00:22:54,590 --> 00:22:57,380
My friend moved out.

192
00:22:57,380 --> 00:23:00,980
I'm sorry, but I don't have time to hang out with you.

193
00:23:00,980 --> 00:23:05,590
As you said, I don't know when I'll be fired, so I need to go practice.

194
00:23:07,830 --> 00:23:11,830
I know a man who owns Colbergs.

195
00:23:16,290 --> 00:23:19,920
You think I wouldn't know that there are only two sets of those timpani in our country?

196
00:23:19,920 --> 00:23:21,870
It's one of them.

197
00:23:21,870 --> 00:23:27,390
He told me it's at his practice room in Gangnam or something.

198
00:23:28,730 --> 00:23:30,560
- For real?
- It's real.

199
00:23:30,560 --> 00:23:33,940
I'm not lying. I'll bet you one of my fingers.

200
00:23:38,930 --> 00:23:41,600
Are you messing with me?

201
00:23:49,840 --> 00:23:53,840
Hold on tight. The engine might turn off as we go.

202
00:23:53,840 --> 00:23:56,140
Don't worry about me and drive—

203
00:23:56,140 --> 00:23:57,970
Excuse me?

204
00:24:10,110 --> 00:24:12,110
We're here.

205
00:24:14,460 --> 00:24:16,180
But...

206
00:24:17,890 --> 00:24:21,830
Why are we here this early in the morning? I thought you said we were going to the practice room.

207
00:24:21,830 --> 00:24:23,820
What practice room?

208
00:24:25,830 --> 00:24:29,270
You said you know the owner of Colbergs.

209
00:24:29,270 --> 00:24:30,870
I do know someone.

210
00:24:33,900 --> 00:24:36,140
You said we were going there!

211
00:24:36,140 --> 00:24:38,110
You even bet your finger. Are we not going?

212
00:24:38,110 --> 00:24:38,750
We're going to go.

213
00:24:38,750 --> 00:24:40,910
- When?
- Let's have some fun first and we can go later.

214
00:24:40,910 --> 00:24:43,440
I just need to keep my promise, right?

215
00:24:48,310 --> 00:24:50,740
Why aren't you coming?

216
00:24:52,530 --> 00:24:54,080
Where are we going?

217
00:24:54,080 --> 00:24:57,250
To take a cable car. Hurry up!

218
00:24:57,250 --> 00:25:01,310
What? A cable car?

219
00:25:01,310 --> 00:25:02,930
Are we going for a ride now?

220
00:25:02,930 --> 00:25:05,220
Hurry up and come.

221
00:25:07,980 --> 00:25:12,860
♫ Stay with me, I hear your voice ♫

222
00:25:12,860 --> 00:25:15,730
Hurry up!
♫ The stressful days also ♫

223
00:25:15,730 --> 00:25:16,820
♫ have all disappeared ♫

224
00:25:16,820 --> 00:25:18,620
No, but why in the morning?

225
00:25:18,620 --> 00:25:21,040
I couldn't even sleep, now he wants me to run up Namsan?
♫ I hope it's not ♫

226
00:25:21,040 --> 00:25:23,080
♫ a moment's dream ♫

227
00:25:23,080 --> 00:25:28,430
♫ I'm in love, I'm in love, I'm glad to have you ♫

228
00:25:28,430 --> 00:25:31,060
♫ What you need? I'm not broken ♫

229
00:25:31,060 --> 00:25:32,220
♫ After a few years ♫

230
00:25:32,220 --> 00:25:34,000
Wait for me!

231
00:25:34,000 --> 00:25:35,680
♫ My impatience just picks anything ♫

232
00:25:35,680 --> 00:25:38,390
♫ Walking fast is my habit ♫

233
00:25:38,390 --> 00:25:41,180
♫ My body is still living inside my dream ♫

234
00:25:41,180 --> 00:25:43,700
♫ Even if I go to the same places, the feeling is different ♫

235
00:25:43,700 --> 00:25:46,490
♫ Even on days that do not require much thinking ♫

236
00:25:46,490 --> 00:25:49,690
♫ I guess I always had a lot on my mind that's why I hurry and go to the next question ♫

237
00:25:49,690 --> 00:25:50,450
♫ I want to know ♫

238
00:25:50,450 --> 00:25:52,640
♫ your next sentence to know how it lines up ♫

239
00:25:52,640 --> 00:25:55,000
♫ You stop me from talking and confuse my mind ♫

240
00:25:55,000 --> 00:25:57,960
♫ I want my pride back, the mistake that you made because of me ♫

241
00:25:57,960 --> 00:26:01,270
♫ But now, I keep stuttering, nah, oh yeah ♫

242
00:26:01,270 --> 00:26:05,630
♫ Stay with me, I hear your voice ♫

243
00:26:05,630 --> 00:26:11,660
♫ The stressful days have all disappeared ♫

244
00:26:11,660 --> 00:26:16,340
♫ I hope it's not a moment's dream ♫

245
00:26:16,340 --> 00:26:22,810
♫ I'm in love, I'm in love, I'm glad to have you ♫

246
00:26:40,600 --> 00:26:44,790
